{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_54","type":"command_execution","command":"/run/current-system/sw/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' ralph-burning-rewrite/20260311192329-impl-notes.md && printf '\\\\n---\\\\n' && sed -n '1,220p' ralph-burning-rewrite/20260311193151-impl-response-001.md\"","aggregated_output":"# Implementation Notes\n\n## Decisions Made\n- Added `WorkspaceSettings` and `PromptReviewSettings` as optional persisted config blocks, with unknown `[settings]` keys preserved through `serde` flattening and `toml_edit` mutation.\n- Centralized config reads in `workspace_governance::EffectiveConfig::load`, which resolves compiled defaults plus `workspace.toml` overrides and tracks per-key value sources for `config show`.\n- Kept file side effects behind `FileSystem`, including atomic config writes, active-project pointer IO, and editor launching for `config edit`.\n- Allowed `config set default_backend|default_model` to clear overrides with `unset`, `none`, or `null`, since those keys are optional in the persisted schema.\n\n## Spec Deviations\n- Validation strictness settings mentioned in the feature description were not added in this slice because the acceptance criteria and file list only defined the typed schema/CLI behavior for `prompt_review.enabled`, `default_flow`, `default_backend`, and `default_model`.\n\n## Testing\n- Verified config defaults, override merging, extended `workspace.toml` round-trip behavior, unknown-key preservation, invalid key/value rejection, and active-project missing/read/write cases in new unit tests.\n- Verified CLI behavior for `config show/get/set/edit` and `project select` in integration tests, including editor revalidation failure handling.\n- Ran `nix develop -c cargo test`.\n- Ran `nix develop -c cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings`.\n\n---\n\n---\n# Implementation Response (Iteration 1)\n\n## Changes Made\n1. Hardened project ID handling for active-project safety by rejecting path-like values in [`src/shared/domain.rs`](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/domain.rs) before any filesystem lookup or pointer write. This now blocks `.` / `..`, `/`, and `\\` in `ProjectId::new`, which covers both `project select` and `resolve_active_project`; matching unit and CLI regressions were added in [`tests/unit/domain_test.rs`](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/domain_test.rs), [`tests/unit/active_project_test.rs`](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/active_project_test.rs), and [`tests/cli.rs`](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/cli.rs).\n2. Fixed `config edit` editor precedence in [`src/adapters/fs.rs`](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/fs.rs) so `$EDITOR` is preferred before `$VISUAL`, with a CLI regression test in [`tests/cli.rs`](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/cli.rs) that sets both variables and verifies the `$EDITOR` script wins. Verification passed with `nix develop --command bash -lc 'cargo test'` and `nix develop --command bash -lc 'cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings'`.\n\n## Could Not Address\n- None\n\n## Pending Changes (Pre-Commit)\n- Uncommitted loop 3 review-response fixes are present in the workspace, including the new artifact file and the validated code/test changes above.\n\n---\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
